[[Category:Coursera]][[Category:SatelliteCommunications]]
**[https://www.coursera.org/minestelecom Institut Mines-Télécom]** [https://www.coursera.org/learn/satellite-communications Description and dates] [https://www.coursera.org/learn/satellite-communications Go to class]

How is a satellite built? How do they fly? How do they communicate and how does the network operate? You will get all the answers in this course from teachers and researchers from three schools associated with Institut Mines-Télécom.

*Please format the transcripts into paragraphs (headings optional), fix errors, and add to the "SatComm Subtitles" and "Subtitles" categories. Here is a [[SatComm Template: Individual |template for individual videos]] and here's one for each [[SatComm Template: Weekly|week]].*

*Place summaries and key points in the main week's page, and copy the summaries here ahead of the list of transcripts.*

*Thank you all for helping create this useful resource*

